        <div class="prose">
            <p>We arrive in Paris in the blue hour of a January afternoon, jet-lagged and giddy, the city spreading out beneath the plane like a map of promises. The apartment is in the 9th, that perfect Parisian neighborhood that tourists rarely find—far enough from the crowds to feel like a secret, close enough to everything to feel like the center of the world.</p>
            
            <p>The first day is for recovery. For walking slowly through unfamiliar streets, for finding the corner café that will become ours, for remembering how to breathe in a different rhythm.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="lodging">
            <div class="lodging__name">Airbnb</div>
            <div class="lodging__address">2 Rue Moncey, Paris 75009</div>
        </div>

        <div class="prose prose--no-dropcap">
            <h3>The Days</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="day">
            <div class="day__header">
                <span class="day__name">Wednesday, January 7</span>
            </div>
            <p>Morning at the <strong>Maison Européenne de la Photographie</strong>—three floors of images that will change how we see. Then across the river to the <strong>Orangerie</strong>, where Monet's Water Lilies wrap around us like a meditation. Walk through the Tuileries in the gray winter light, then lose ourselves in Saint-Germain for dinner.</p>
            <p><em>Shopping: UNIQLO for basics, Lemaire for something beautiful, Merci for gifts we'll pretend are for others.</em></p>
        </div>

        <div class="day">
            <div class="day__header">
                <span class="day__name">Thursday, January 8</span>
            </div>
            <p>A free morning. Perhaps the Marais, perhaps nothing at all. We leave for Venice tomorrow.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

