        <div class="prose">
            <p>From the canals of Venice to the peaks of the Dolomites—a journey from water to stone, from Renaissance to sublime. We're splitting this mountain time between two extraordinary places: Cortina d'Ampezzo, the glamorous queen of the Dolomites, and Alpe di Siusi, Europe's largest alpine meadow where the Sassolungo and Sciliar peaks rise like cathedrals of rock.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="callout">
            <p class="callout__text">"The mountains are calling and I must go."</p>
        </div>

        <div class="prose prose--no-dropcap">
            <h3>Cortina d'Ampezzo · Jan 13–15</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="lodging">
            <div class="lodging__name">Rosapetra SPA Resort</div>
            <div class="lodging__address">Zuel di Sopra 1, Cortina d'Ampezzo</div>
            <div class="lodging__conf">+39 0436 869062</div>
        </div>

        <div class="day">
            <div class="day__header">
                <span class="day__name">Tuesday, January 13</span>
            </div>
            <p>Travel from Venice to Cortina. The train winds through the foothills, the Dolomites growing in the windows until they fill the sky. Check-in, first spa session, early dinner. The mountains will still be there tomorrow.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="day">
            <div class="day__header">
                <span class="day__name">Wednesday, January 14</span>
            </div>
            <p>A spa day with options. Morning in the thermal pools, afternoon for a gentle winter walk or simply reading by the fire. This is the Dolomites in rest mode—letting the landscape do the work.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="prose prose--no-dropcap">
            <h3>Alpe di Siusi · Jan 15–17</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="lodging">
            <div class="lodging__name">COMO Alpina Dolomites</div>
            <div class="lodging__address">Compatsch 62/3, Castelrotto</div>
            <div class="lodging__conf">Conf#43877SF040353</div>
        </div>

        <div class="day">
            <div class="day__header">
                <span class="day__name">Thursday, January 15</span>
            </div>
            <p>Transfer to Alpe di Siusi. The drive climbs through pine forests and emerges onto the plateau like entering another world. Afternoon to explore the meadow—by foot, by sled, by simply standing still and looking.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="day">
            <div class="day__header">
                <span class="day__name">Friday, January 16</span>
            </div>
            <p>Mountain day. Winter hiking to a <strong>rifugio</strong> for lunch—those mountain huts where they serve polenta and speck and wine that tastes better than anything in the valley. Back for spa, dinner, and the last night in the Dolomites.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="day">
            <div class="day__header">
                <span class="day__name">Saturday, January 17</span>
            </div>
            <p>One more spa session, then the long train to Milan. We'll arrive by evening and maybe, if we have energy, visit <strong>Pirelli HangarBicocca</strong>—that vast industrial cathedral of contemporary art, free and open late on Saturdays.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

